What a click bait title  lol. 

Stating Intel steals AMD thing lol. You do realize that resizable bar was NOT invented by AMD right?? Resizable bar is part of PCIe 3.0 standard so any motherboard that has PCIe 3.0 is resizable bar enhanced and can also have the graphics card let the CPU access 100% of its Vram instead of 250mb or whatever size at any given time. They are just now enabling it for the Intel ecosystem for the CPU to utilize 100% of the GCs VRAM.

Its like PEOPLE saying AMD big navi GC are  stealing  "RayTracing" from Nvidia. What people dont know is This technology and the name "ray tracing" DOES not belong to NVIDA. The technology exist to both graph cards and they both are capable of doing raytracing. Now Nvidia just does it better bc they implemented more of these raytracing cores in their chips. 

Now if AMD implements DLSS  in their GPUs and you stated that AMD is stealing NVIDIAs thing THEN that statement it correct bc DLSS is specific and created solely by NVIDA.

snippet.textDisplay:
Back in the day when ham radio wasn't _just_ a bunch of old farts, we had ways of dealing with people who could not behave in a civil manner. One of them was "cable pinning" their antenna. This consisted of shoving pins through the cable to short it out, and then trimming off the ends so they can't be seen. This is done multiple times. The next time they hit the button to transmit, they'll let the magic smoke out.

It might take something a bit more overt than pinning a cable, but I am of the opinion that damaging someone's equipment to stop an attack on your infrastructure is absolutely ethical. If they are an innocent party who has had their gear hijacked, perhaps that will be the end of their involvement. If not, repeat visits may be required. If your router is busy blowing up the Internet because it is pwn3d, tough luck over the financial cost. You didn't secure it, and it got weaponized. Now it must be destroyed to protect everyone else.
